istrators     Help     Sandbox     Recent Changes                          in: Wizards, Burkinabé Ministers for Magic, Males, Seekers         English     Deutsch   Español   Français   Polski   Русский               Joshua Sankara              View source                         History                         Talk (0)                                   Joshua Sankara   Biographical information  Born Before 1989, Burkina Faso   Nationality Burkinabé   Title(s) SeekerMinister for Magic (formerly)    Physical information  Species Human   Gender Male    Affiliation  Occupation Seeker for Burkina FasoMinister for Magic (formerly)   Loyalty Burkinabé National Quidditch teamBurkinabé Ministry of Magic (formerly)   [Source]  Minister Joshua Sankara was a Burkinabé wizard who played as Seeker for the Burkinabé National Quidditch team, and was also briefly Burkina Faso's Minister for Magic in 2006.[1]  Contents  1 Biography 2 Behind the scenes 3 Appearances 4 Notes and references   Biography Sankara was born sometime in Burkina Faso. He likely attended Uagadou during his youth. At some point, he became the Seeker for the Burkinabé National Quidditch team for the 2006 Quidditch World Cup, during which his team got to the finals alongside France, a match that Burkina Faso would win. After his team won the World Cup, Sankara was named Minister for Magic, though he resigned two days later as he much rathered to play Quidditch than hold office at the Burkinabé Ministry of Magic.[1]  Behind the scenes He may be named after Thomas Sankara, a former president of Burkina Faso. Appearances Pottermore (First mentioned) Notes and references   ↑ 1.0 1.1  Pottermore - Quidditch World Cup 1990 - 2014 (Archived)     Quidditch positions      Keeper   Raul Almeida · Ralph Heidelberger · Jonny Nuhaka · Lev Zograf · Denison Frisby · Bastien Janvier · Hermann Wiel · Barry Ryan · Tamotsu Iwamoto · Darren O'Hare · Martin Helstrom · Oliver Wood · Sendelina de la Felino · Merwyn Finwick  ·  Parkin · 